Author:  HUNT
Vol / Page:  20
Edition:
Quote:  Our chief source of revenue was to gather in the bush fungus, which usually grew upon the dead and partly decayed stems of karaka and mahoe trees, dry it in the open air, and sell it to the Chinese merchants
